ğŸš† Train Ticket Reservation System

A mini-app built with Go, gRPC, and PostgreSQL. It features a modern microservices architecture with a web bridge allowing users to book, modify, and cancel train tickets through a browser.

ğŸš€ Features
gRPC API: High-performance communication between the web server and the backend.

Web Dashboard: Accessible on port 8888 (to avoid Jenkins/8080 conflicts).

Persistence: PostgreSQL database stores all reservations.

Containerized: Fully Dockerized for easy deployment.

CRUD Operations: Create (Book), Read (View), Update (Modify), and Delete (Cancel) tickets.

ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack
Language: Go (Golang)

Communication: gRPC & Protocol Buffers

Database: PostgreSQL 15

Containerization: Docker & Docker Compose

Frontend: HTML5 / CSS3

