âš™ï¸ Setup & Installation
1. Prerequisites
Docker & Docker Desktop installed.

Go 1.21+ (if running locally).

2. Run with Docker (Recommended)
This is the easiest way to start the entire stack.


# Clone the repository
git clone <your-repo-link>
cd ticket_booking_app

# Start the application
docker compose up --build



Once the logs show the services are ready, open your browser at: ğŸ‘‰ http://localhost:8888

3. Running Locally (Development)
If you want to run the code without Docker, ensure you have a PostgreSQL instance running and set the DATABASE_URL environment variable.


# Get dependencies
go mod tidy

# Run Server
go run server/main.go

# Run Web UI (in another terminal)
go run web/main.go


ğŸ“¡ API Endpoints (gRPC)
The gRPC server listens on :50051 and supports:

ReserveTicket: Creates a new booking.

ModifyTicket: Changes seat/section for an existing ticket ID.

CancelTicket: Removes a ticket from the database.

ğŸ“ Usage Notes
Port 8888: The Web UI is mapped to 8888 to prevent conflicts with Jenkins or other local services.

Database: Data is persisted in a Docker volume named postgres_data. Even if you stop the containers, your tickets remain safe.